| Duration | Exercise | Intensity | Notes |
|----------|----------|-----------|-------|
| 1 min | Warm‑up jog | 60% | Light pace, easy breathing |
| 1 min | Body‑weight squats | 80% | Maintain form, knees tracking toes |
| 1 min | Stationary lunges | 80% | 30 sec each leg, keep core tight |
| 1 min | Jumping jacks | 90% | Full‑range arms, keep hips square |
| **1 min** | **Sprint** | **140% intensity** | Push at maximum safe speed; keep shoulders relaxed |
| 1 min | Mountain climbers | 90% | Drive knees, keep hips low |
| 1 min | Wall sit | 85% | Hold, breathe evenly |
| 1 min | Single‑leg hops | 80% | 30 sec per leg, focus on balance |
| 1 min | Tuck jumps | 95% | Soft landing, knees slightly bent |

| 1 min | Cool‑down slow jog | 60% | Gradually lower heart rate |

battle_log.defender_output:
**15‑Minute HIIT Leg‑Day Workout**

| Time | Exercise | Intensity | Key Focus |
|------|----------|-----------|-----------|
| **1 min** | Warm‑up jog | 60 % | Light pace, steady breathing |
| **1 min** | Body‑weight squats | 80 % | Keep knees tracking toes, hips stacked over ankles |
| **1 min** | Stationary lunges | 80 % | 30 s each leg, core tight, 90° knee angle at bottom |
| **1 min** | Jumping jacks | 90 % | Full arm swing, hips square |
| **1 min** | Sprint | 140 % | Push max safe pace, shoulders relaxed, engage core |
| **1 min** | Mountain climbers | 90 % | Pull knees in rhythm, hips low, arms straight |
| **1 min** | Wall sit | 85 % | 30 s per leg, breath even, elbows straight |
| **1 min** | Single‑leg hops | 80 % | 30 s each leg, balance, soft knees |
| **1 min** | Tuck jumps | 95 % | Soft landing, knees slightly bent |
| **1 min** | Quick‑step side shuffles | 90 % | Light on toes, keep hips low |
| **1 min** | Cool‑down slow jog | 60 % | Gradual heart‑rate drop |
| **1 min** | Static stretching (quads, hamstrings, calves) | – | Hold each stretch 45 s, breathe deeply |

**Total: 15 minutes**

> **Safety Tips:**  
> • Stay hydrated; sip water before, during, and after the session.  
> • Keep form above speed—poor technique can lead to injury.  
> • Listen to your body; if any exercise causes sharp pain, stop and reassess.  
> • Rest for 10–15 seconds between each minute if needed, but aim to keep the flow continuous to maintain cardiovascular benefit.  

Enjoy the burn and give your legs the power‑boost they deserve!
